      "lineNbr": 141,
      "author": {
        "id": 1134874
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-13T17:31:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Done\n\nIn particular: we try to unmarshal json.RawMessage to TestFields. It won\u0027t fail even if it\u0027s an intermediate node, because unknown fields are ignored, and missing fields are not populated.\n\nInstead, we check that the \"actual\" and \"expected\" fields are not empty strings. Right now it\u0027s inlined, since checking the fields in a list would otherwise require reflection, and there are only two.\n\nChan, do you think it makes sense to check \"actual\" and \"expected\" /only/? If so, how do you feel about it being inlined, vs. pulled out into a helper function? I don\u0027t mind either way.",
      "parentUuid": "b4a88158_5fab1354",
      "range": {
